Seongjun Hong is an undergraduate student at Sogang University, majoring in Mathematics with a minor in Electrical Engineering, and is expected to graduate in February 2026. He is particularly interested in memory systems within CPU and GPU architectures. Currently, he is an undergraduate research intern at GAUDI Lab, where he is gaining hands-on experience in architectural research and exploring methods to enhance performance and efficiency. Seongjun is enthusiastic about deepening his understanding of these systems and contributing to advancements in the field.
